\begin_layout Standard
Conventional wisdom assumes that growth stocks (firms with low B/M ratio)
 are riskier stocks, but they earn lower returns than value stocks (high
 B/M ratio).
 This is called the 
\emph on
value premium 
\emph default
in literature.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
